About SYSTRA Canada
SYSTRA Canada is part of the SYSTRA Group, an international consulting and engineering group, a world leader in the design of transport infrastructures. SYSTRA Canada is an engineering and consulting firm who is dedicated to transportation solutions, whether for passengers or goods.
Imagining and implementing the safest, most efficient, and economical tailor-made transport solutions: this is what guides us daily. Thanks to the know-how of our 7500 experts, we are involved in all phases of transport projects: Preliminary and design studies, construction phases, test and commissioning, operation, and maintenance.
Our engineers work with passion to provide people around the world with the opportunity to move freely every day. They are men and women who put all their business expertise and human qualities to work to transform the world through innovative means of transport. Join them and let's invent tomorrow's public transport together.
SYSTRA's ambition is to be the benchmark for transport solutions and an opinion leader in mobility.
Role and responsibilities
Reporting to the Financial Controller and based at the Montreal head office, the General Accountant is responsible for preparing monthly and annual financial statements of the company and its divisions.
Main responsibilities are:
Responsible for the complete monthly and annual accounting closing process in the ERP;
Produce financial statements, monthly, quarterly and annual reports as well as all financial information for management, shareholders, tax authorities and financial institutions;
Participate in the development of the schedule of closing activities;
Perform monthly financial analyses and account reconciliations;
Perform bank reconciliations and validation of bank charges billed;
Fixed assets: the creation of codes, coding of invoices and archiving of invoices/contracts related to fixed assets;
Coordinate, establish and record accounting transactions in the various journals;
Follow-up and control of accounting operations of foreign branches;
Maintain in ERP the exchange rates, accounting accounts and other rules that need to be modified as needed;
Validation of the accounting coding of purchase orders and creation of supplier files in the ERP;
Validation of payment requests from branches to suppliers and calls for funds;
Responsible for establishing hourly rates for employees of foreign branches and recording them in the ERP;
Produce GST, HST and QST sales tax returns;
Supervision, control and validation of the production of reports required by the tax authorities of the foreign branches on a monthly, quarterly or annual basis;
Ensure the timely payment of taxes, duties and fees required by the tax and administrative authorities of foreign branches;
Participate in the development of internal control policies and procedures;
Participate in the development of documentation for accounting procedures in the ERP system;
Participate and assist the financial controller during internal and external audits;
Participate in the preparation of the company's annual budgets and their revisions;
Participate in projects to improve accounting and financial tools or others.
Other
Ensure compliance with company policies, internal procedures and accounting standards;
Support to other accounting team members and internal stakeholders;
Ensure that all documentation relating to accounting transactions is archived and stored according to the rules in force;
Other related duties.
Qualifications
Education:
Undergraduate degree in accounting
Years of experience:
5 years of experience in a similar position
Technical competencies:
Recognized accounting designation;
Experience in a project-based accounting environment;
Experience in an ERP environment;
Knowledge of Microsoft Excel and PowerPoint advanced tools;
Excellent knowledge of French and English, oral and written.
Personal & soft skills:
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills;
Excellent planning and organizational skills;
Very good analytical and synthesis skills;
Good level of autonomy, initiative and ability to work in a team;
Critical thinking skills to develop innovative solutions.
